body:
@szetszwo  

hmm I have thought about that. For current test setup it is ok. Because the data structure is `ConcurrentMap<RaftGroupId, MultiDataStreamStateMachine>` and currently each client uses a random group id, so sharing the same map among servers does not overwrite each other thus it is still working. 

For the multiple group change, I will need to update this test because in that change, servers will share the same group id so they cannot share the same map anymore.

@szetszwo Could you help review this ? 

> The RaftClientRequest seems already the same across servers as shown in runTestDataStream(..). No?
> 
> //DataStreamBaseTest.runTestDataStream
>       for (Server s : servers) {
>         assertHeader(s, out.getHeader(), dataSize);
>       }

The test is not strong to cover the same RaftClientRequest, we should add     `Assert.assertEquals(writeRequest.getClientId(), header.getClientId());`

@runzhiwang thanks a lot for reviewing this.

@amaliujia , you may want to combine small change like this with another JIRA such as RATIS-1130.  Otherwise, it will be inefficient.

Also, we would like to split a large change into multiple JIRAs.  Otherwise, it is not easy to review.  Changes with size (generated "git diff") between 10KB and 20KB probably is the optimal.  :)

@szetszwo I have updated the patch. Could you help review it again ? Besides,  I think with the commit https://github.com/apache/incubator-ratis/commit/05eaa70128dfa12dcfed459684983267cb079e92, CI is easier to pass,  most of the previous CI failed reason is port conflict, I will continue to find the root cause.

> We should also think about how to send exceptions back to the client when there are the exceptions caught in code.

I will do it in next PR.

> @runzhiwang
> Tests can pass locally so the failed CL might not be related to this PR. If there is still issues after rerun I will definitely take a deeper look.

@amaliujia Now we merge PR  when it pass CI.
